Reddit launched its r/thebutton thread on April Fool's Day and placed a button next to a 60-second timer . 
  More than 730,285 users have pressed The Button since the thread launched . 
  When The Button is clicked, the timer resets to 60 seconds . 
  Only people who registered on the site before 1 April are eligible to click The Button . 
  When they do they are awarded a colour, known as a 'flair . 
 ' This colour represents the time period at which they clicked the button . 
  Users can only press The Button once and receive a coloured flair . 
 